                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Depends on the mobs you're charming as to whether you're gonna run or stand.
<br />

<br />
eg. If I'm soloing & have reasonable buffs up a hasted elemental level pet hitting for regular 600+'s is not something I like waiting to get into range of, even with 8k buffed hp and runes. Levi + sow, then run using the contours of the walls to increase your distance on ex-pet (i.e. you straightline it, mob goes up and down over rocks) and then re-charm.
<br />

<br />
Congratulations, you have just solo charm kited.
<br />

<br />
Also, try this.... 3-4 encs, druid, ranger..... 3-4 encs all get charmed pets. Pull mob, too many people on agro and it will always go after someone, ignoring charm pets....Said person runs around with mob following them and pets following mob. Group charm kiting.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=521573" target="_blank" class="postlink">Nop)</a>
<br />

<br />
E65.740/EM h+ 5557khp 7079km ft18 G++++! e++++ o+ T+++ L H- f-- g+ b- c++ !t D X-</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
