                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">"charm kiting" is a particular way that bards solo. It involves pulling a bunch of mobs, then charming one and having the rest beat on it until charm wears off, then running. You keep doing that until all of the mobs are low, then you ae them down, or something. The key features are:
<br />

<br />
1) lots of mobs
<br />
2) charming one for the purpose of having the rest beat on it
<br />

<br />
This is distinct from normal charming because you're not using your charmed pet offensively, you're charming for the purpose of wearing the pet down so you can easily kill it when charm breaks. Enchanters can't really do this because our charm takes too long to cast and can't be cast on the run.
<br />

<br />
Recent changes to the way agro works may have made this a lot less effective, but I can remember bards doing it a long time ago with great success.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6057" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kanvil Shadowleaf</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.eternalsovereign.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Eternal Sovereign</a>
<br />
Tholuxe Paells</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
